sdp/prd-snapshot.md:1:# PRD Snapshot - PAL 2026 Agentic Operations Platform PRD
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:2:**Source:** `sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md`
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:7:# PAL 2026 Agentic Operations Platform PRD
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:9:**Project:** PromptClaw / PAL 2026
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:14:**PAL project root:** `pal-2026/`
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:15:**Live PAL target:** Vast.ai A6000 node `pal-cloud-a6000` over Tailscale
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:22:PAL 2026 Phase 1 is already online as a basic inference and operations target:
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:26:- PromptClaw has PAL client commands for health, query, smoke tests, baseline summaries, triage, and approval-gated actions.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:27:- Live smoke and triage runs have produced normal PromptClaw artifacts under `pal-2026/.promptclaw/runs/`.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:29:The current implementation is a useful foundation but is not yet the full "minimal operator involvement" PAL system. This PRD defines the end-to-end build needed to let SDP frontier models implement, verify, and deploy a complete PAL 2026 agentic operations platform.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:31:The intended outcome is not that PAL becomes an unrestricted shell agent. The intended outcome is that PAL can:
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:33:1. Maintain a project knowledge base from PAL docs, runbooks, smoke reports, deployment state, and run artifacts.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:41:This PRD should be loaded into SDP after validation. The SDP frontier models should build this, not the current PAL model.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:49:- `promptclaw/pal_client.py`: stdlib client for PAL router `/health` and `/query`.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:50:- `promptclaw/pal_smoke.py`: fixed PAL smoke suite and smoke baseline summaries.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:51:- `promptclaw/pal_agent.py`: bounded PAL ops triage and approval-gated actions.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:59:- PAL project config in `pal-2026/promptclaw.json` with `pal.enabled=true`.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:61:The live PAL host is currently host-managed, not Docker-managed:
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:80:1. Build PAL into a complete agentic operations layer for the current Phase 1 deployment.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:82:3. Make every PAL decision reproducible through PromptClaw artifacts.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:83:4. Let SDP agents implement and verify this end to end with unit tests, CLI integration tests, and live PAL probes.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:84:5. Add deployment automation that can safely update the live PAL host and verify it after deploy.
sdp/prd-snapshot.md:103:PAL should proceed without asking Anthony for routine implementation details, test runs, docs edits, health checks, smoke runs, read-only SSH inspections, and artifact generation.
