docs/coherence-foundations.md:54:- **Declarative source-of-truth (GitOps reconciliation).** The GitOps pattern --- where the declared state in version control is the only source of truth, and all runtime state is derived from it --- prevents state drift between what agents believe and what actually exists.
docs/coherence-foundations.md:70:- **Temporal knowledge graphs (Zep/Graphiti).** Graphiti achieves 94.8% accuracy on temporal knowledge tasks by modeling facts as graph edges with time ranges. This matters for decision memory because decisions can be superseded --- the system must know not just what was decided but *when* it was valid.
docs/coherence-foundations.md:126:Event-sourced state management where the complete system state can be reconstructed by replaying the event log. Achieved 72% on SWE-bench. **Lesson for PromptClaw:** Event sourcing is the correct state model for multi-agent systems. PromptClaw's `EventStoreBackend` protocol and append-only log are directly inspired by this architecture.
